Implement Phase 36: zDash Server Command Center + Secret-Safe Git Workflow.

Context:
The current Makefile already includes many install, production, validation, Codex, infra, Docker, release, and cleanup targets.

Current Makefile already has:
- install-local
- install-local-start
- install-local-pull
- install-local-fast
- install-local-docker
- install-repair
- install-validate
- install-health
- install-prod
- install-prod-tests
- install-prod-no-firewall
- prod-ps
- prod-health
- prod-logs
- prod-backend-logs
- prod-nginx-logs
- prod-backup
- prod-update
- prod-start
- prod-stop
- prod-restart
- prod-status
- prod-up
- prod-down
- codex-setup
- codex-maintenance
- codex-repair-backend
- codex-healthcheck
- script-run-phases
- script-export-json-prompt
- script-integrate-ecc
- script-sync-ecc-codex
- script-setup-dev
- script-enable-agents
- infra-deploy-dev
- infra-deploy-prod
- infra-rollback
- validate-fast
- validate
- run-backend
- run-frontend

Do not duplicate existing targets.
Do not re-add prod-up, prod-down, prod-ps, prod-logs, or prod-health if they already exist.
Do not create duplicate Makefile recipes.
Keep make help clean with no override warnings.

Goal:
Add a clean server command layer and secret-safe Git workflow for local Ubuntu/VMware development and safe push to GitHub.

Hard safety requirements:
- Do not enable live trading.
- Keep DRY_RUN=true by default.
- Keep LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false.
- Keep MT5_ENABLED=false.
- Keep PRODUCTION_ALLOW_LIVE_ACTIONS=false.
- Keep RISK_GUARDIAN_ENABLED=true.
- Do not add real broker execution.
- Do not add real AWS, OpenAI, GitHub, Cloudflare, broker, or database secrets.
- Do not weaken GitHub push protection.
- Do not bypass safety-scan.
- Do not bypass high-risk action policy.
- Do not commit Makefile.bak.* or local backup files.

Part 1: Add local server scripts

Create directory:

scripts/server/

Create files:

scripts/server/start-local.sh
scripts/server/stop-local.sh
scripts/server/status-local.sh
scripts/server/logs-local.sh
scripts/server/open-local.sh

Requirements:

start-local.sh:
- Must start backend and frontend in background.
- Backend:
  - cd backend
  - source .venv/bin/activate
  - run uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port ${BACKEND_PORT:-8005}
- Frontend:
  - use nvm if available
  - use Node ${NODE_VERSION:-20}
  - cd frontend
  - run npm run dev -- --host 0.0.0.0 --port ${FRONTEND_PORT:-5173}
- Create:
  - .runtime/logs/
  - .runtime/pids/
- Write:
  - .runtime/logs/backend.log
  - .runtime/logs/frontend.log
  - .runtime/pids/backend.pid
  - .runtime/pids/frontend.pid
- Must not use pkill.
- Must not kill unrelated uvicorn/vite processes.
- If a PID file exists but process is dead, clean it.
- If server is already running, print status and do not start duplicate process.
- Print local and LAN URLs.
- Check backend /health after start.
- Check frontend root URL after start.
- Clearly print:
  - Backend URL
  - Frontend URL
  - API docs URL
  - log file paths

stop-local.sh:
- Read PIDs only from .runtime/pids.
- Stop only those PIDs.
- Remove PID files after stop.
- Do not use broad pkill.
- Be idempotent.

status-local.sh:
- Show backend/frontend PID status.
- Show open ports 8005 and 5173.
- Show backend /health result if available.
- Show frontend HTTP status if available.
- Show LAN IP from hostname -I.

logs-local.sh:
- Follow both logs by default.
- Support SERVICE=backend or SERVICE=frontend.
- If log file does not exist, print clear message.

open-local.sh:
- Print browser URLs.
- If xdg-open exists and OPEN_BROWSER=true, open frontend URL.
- Default must only print URLs.

Part 2: Add production server wrapper scripts

Create:

scripts/server/start-prod.sh
scripts/server/stop-prod.sh
scripts/server/status-prod.sh
scripts/server/logs-prod.sh

Requirements:

- These scripts must wrap existing production runtime helpers:
  - /opt/zdash/runtime/scripts/zdash-health.sh
  - /opt/zdash/runtime/scripts/zdash-logs.sh
  - /opt/zdash/runtime/scripts/zdash-backup.sh
  - /opt/zdash/runtime/scripts/zdash-update.sh
- If production installer has not been run, fail safely with a clear message:
  “Production runtime not found. Run: sudo ./install-zdash-prod.sh”
- start-prod.sh:
  - sudo systemctl start zdash
  - show systemctl status --no-pager
  - run production health helper if available
- stop-prod.sh:
  - sudo systemctl stop zdash
  - show status
- status-prod.sh:
  - show systemd status
  - show docker compose ps if runtime compose exists
  - show health
- logs-prod.sh:
  - call production log helper
  - support SERVICE=backend/nginx/frontend/postgres/redis

Part 3: Add safe Git scripts

Create directory:

scripts/git/

Create files:

scripts/git/clean-local-artifacts.sh
scripts/git/safe-status.sh
scripts/git/safe-add.sh
scripts/git/safe-commit.sh
scripts/git/safe-push.sh

clean-local-artifacts.sh:
- Remove:
  - Makefile.bak.*
  - *.bak
  - backend.log
  - frontend.log
  - .runtime/tmp/
  - local generated temp files
- Do not remove:
  - source code
  - .env
  - .env.production
  - frontend/.env.local
  - user data directories
- Print removed paths.

safe-status.sh:
- Run:
  - git status --short
  - git diff --stat
  - git diff --cached --stat
- Highlight risky files if staged:
  - .env
  - .env.*
  - *.pem
  - *.key
  - Makefile.bak.*
  - backend.log
  - frontend.log
  - .runtime/
- Do not print secret values.

safe-add.sh:
- Run clean-local-artifacts.sh first.
- Add only safe project files by default.
- Never add:
  - .env
  - .env.*
  - frontend/.env.local
  - Makefile.bak.*
  - *.bak
  - backend.log
  - frontend.log
  - .runtime/
  - node_modules/
  - backend/.venv/
- Support explicit path args:
  scripts/git/safe-add.sh Makefile backend/app/risk/high_risk_policy.py
- Reject unsafe explicit paths with clear error.

safe-commit.sh:
- Accept message through:
  - MESSAGE="..."
  - or first argument
- Before commit:
  - run safe-status.sh
  - run make safety-scan
  - scan staged diff for:
    - AWS access key IDs
    - AWS secret access keys
    - OpenAI keys
    - GitHub tokens
    - Claude/Anthropic keys
    - Cloudflare tokens
    - private keys
- Avoid false-positive blocking for harmless unit test fixture strings.
- If ECC pre-commit blocks a known false positive in test fixtures, print guidance but do not automatically bypass.
- Do not use ECC_SKIP_PRECOMMIT automatically.
- Commit only if checks pass.

safe-push.sh:
- Run:
  - make validate-fast
  - safe-status.sh
- Push:
  - git push origin main
- If GitHub push protection blocks:
  - print exact recovery instructions:
    - git fetch origin main
    - git reset --soft origin/main
    - remove secret from files
    - git add safe files
    - make validate-fast
    - git commit
    - git push origin main
  - remind to rotate/delete leaked cloud keys immediately
- Do not print secret values.
- Do not open unblock URL automatically.

Part 4: Update .gitignore

Ensure these entries exist:

.runtime/
*.bak
Makefile.bak.*
backend.log
frontend.log
.installer-backups/
release-artifacts/
.codex/tmp/
.codex/cache/
.codex/runs/

Do not ignore:
- Makefile
- install-zdash-fullstack.sh
- install-zdash-prod.sh
- scripts/server/*.sh
- scripts/git/*.sh
- backend/app/**
- frontend/src/**

Part 5: Update Makefile without duplication

Important:
Before adding targets, check if a target already exists.
Do not duplicate any target.
Do not create override warnings.

Add these targets only if missing:

server-start:
- bash scripts/server/start-local.sh

server-stop:
- bash scripts/server/stop-local.sh

server-status:
- bash scripts/server/status-local.sh

server-logs:
- SERVICE=$(SERVICE) bash scripts/server/logs-local.sh

server-open:
- bash scripts/server/open-local.sh

server-restart:
- make server-stop
- make server-start

git-clean-local:
- bash scripts/git/clean-local-artifacts.sh

git-safe-status:
- bash scripts/git/safe-status.sh

git-safe-add:
- bash scripts/git/safe-add.sh $(ARGS)

git-safe-commit:
- MESSAGE="$(MESSAGE)" bash scripts/git/safe-commit.sh

git-safe-push:
- bash scripts/git/safe-push.sh

safe-push:
- alias to git-safe-push

safe-commit:
- alias to git-safe-commit

Update help common flows to include:
- make server-start
- make server-status
- make server-logs SERVICE=backend
- make server-stop
- make git-safe-add ARGS="Makefile backend/app/risk/high_risk_policy.py"
- make git-safe-commit MESSAGE="Fix validation scan"
- make git-safe-push

Keep existing targets:
- install-local
- install-local-start
- install-prod
- prod-health
- prod-logs
- run-backend
- run-frontend
- validate-fast

Do not rename existing targets.

